// Example(2D): We'll use this shape in several examples
//   ushape = [[-10, 0],[-10, 10],[ -7, 10],[ -7, 2],[  7, 2],[  7, 7],[ 10, 7],[ 10, 0]];
//   polygon(ushape);
// Example: Sweep along a clockwise elliptical arc, using default "incremental" method.
